## Cryptographic Guidelines

### Recommended Libraries

| Purpose | Recommended | Avoid |
|---------|-------------|-------|
| General crypto | `ring`, `RustCrypto` | Custom implementations |
| Password hashing | `argon2`, `scrypt` | `bcrypt` (older), MD5, SHA1 |
| Symmetric encryption | `aes-gcm`, `chacha20poly1305` | AES-ECB, DES |
| Asymmetric crypto | `ed25519-dalek`, `x25519-dalek` | RSA < 2048 bits |
| Random numbers | `rand`, `getrandom` | `rand::thread_rng` for crypto |

### Encryption Patterns

```rust
use aes_gcm::{
    aead::{Aead, KeyInit, OsRng},
    Aes256Gcm, Nonce,
};

/// Encrypt data using AES-256-GCM
fn encrypt(key: &[u8; 32], plaintext: &[u8]) -> Result<Vec<u8>, Error> {
    let cipher = Aes256Gcm::new_from_slice(key)
        .map_err(|_| Error::InvalidKey)?;

    // Generate random nonce - NEVER reuse nonces!
    let mut nonce_bytes = [0u8; 12];
    getrandom::getrandom(&mut nonce_bytes)?;
    let nonce = Nonce::from_slice(&nonce_bytes);

    let ciphertext = cipher.encrypt(nonce, plaintext)
        .map_err(|_| Error::EncryptionFailed)?;

    // Prepend nonce to ciphertext
    let mut result = nonce_bytes.to_vec();
    result.extend(ciphertext);
    Ok(result)
}

/// Decrypt data using AES-256-GCM
fn decrypt(key: &[u8; 32], ciphertext: &[u8]) -> Result<Vec<u8>, Error> {
    if ciphertext.len() < 12 {
        return Err(Error::InvalidCiphertext);
    }

    let cipher = Aes256Gcm::new_from_slice(key)
        .map_err(|_| Error::InvalidKey)?;

    let nonce = Nonce::from_slice(&ciphertext[..12]);
    let plaintext = cipher.decrypt(nonce, &ciphertext[12..])
        .map_err(|_| Error::DecryptionFailed)?;

    Ok(plaintext)
}
```

### Password Hashing

```rust
use argon2::{
    password_hash::{PasswordHash, PasswordHasher, PasswordVerifier, SaltString},
    Argon2,
};

/// Hash a password using Argon2id
fn hash_password(password: &str) -> Result<String, Error> {
    let salt = SaltString::generate(&mut OsRng);
    let argon2 = Argon2::default();

    let hash = argon2.hash_password(password.as_bytes(), &salt)
        .map_err(|_| Error::HashingFailed)?;

    Ok(hash.to_string())
}

/// Verify a password against a hash
fn verify_password(password: &str, hash: &str) -> Result<bool, Error> {
    let parsed = PasswordHash::new(hash)
        .map_err(|_| Error::InvalidHash)?;

    Ok(Argon2::default()
        .verify_password(password.as_bytes(), &parsed)
        .is_ok())
}
```

### Constant-Time Comparisons

```rust
use subtle::ConstantTimeEq;

/// Compare two byte slices in constant time
fn secure_compare(a: &[u8], b: &[u8]) -> bool {
    if a.len() != b.len() {
        return false;
    }
    a.ct_eq(b).into()
}

// NEVER use regular comparison for secrets
fn insecure_compare(a: &[u8], b: &[u8]) -> bool {
    a == b // Timing side-channel!
}
```

