## Dependency Security

### Auditing Dependencies

Run these checks regularly:

```bash
# Check for known vulnerabilities
cargo audit

# Check licenses and bans
cargo deny check

# Measure unsafe code in dependencies
cargo geiger

# Verify dependency integrity
cargo vet
```

### Cargo.toml Best Practices

```toml
[dependencies]
# Pin to specific versions for security-critical deps
ring = "=0.17.5"
aes-gcm = "=0.10.3"

# Use version ranges for less critical deps
serde = "1.0"
tokio = { version = "1", features = ["rt-multi-thread"] }

# Minimize features to reduce attack surface
reqwest = { version = "0.11", default-features = false, features = ["rustls-tls"] }
```

### deny.toml Configuration

```toml
[advisories]
vulnerability = "deny"
unmaintained = "warn"
yanked = "deny"

[licenses]
allow = ["MIT", "Apache-2.0", "BSD-3-Clause"]
copyleft = "deny"

[bans]
multiple-versions = "warn"
deny = [
    { name = "openssl" },  # Prefer rustls
    { name = "native-tls" },
]
```

