## Error Handling

### Don't Leak Sensitive Information

```rust
// GOOD: Generic error for external callers
#[derive(Error, Debug)]
pub enum AuthError {
    #[error("authentication failed")]
    Failed,
}

// Internal error with details for logging
#[derive(Error, Debug)]
enum InternalAuthError {
    #[error("user not found: {0}")]
    UserNotFound(String),
    #[error("password mismatch for user: {0}")]
    PasswordMismatch(String),
    #[error("account locked: {0}")]
    AccountLocked(String),
}

pub fn authenticate(username: &str, password: &str) -> Result<User, AuthError> {
    match internal_authenticate(username, password) {
        Ok(user) => Ok(user),
        Err(e) => {
            // Log detailed error internally
            tracing::warn!("Auth failed: {}", e);
            // Return generic error externally
            Err(AuthError::Failed)
        }
    }
}
```

### Use Result, Not Panic

```rust
// GOOD: Return Result for fallible operations
pub fn parse_config(input: &str) -> Result<Config, ConfigError> {
    toml::from_str(input).map_err(ConfigError::Parse)
}

// AVOID: Panicking in library code
pub fn bad_parse_config(input: &str) -> Config {
    toml::from_str(input).expect("invalid config") // Don't do this!
}
```

