## Common Vulnerabilities

### CWE-119: Buffer Overflow

```rust
// VULNERABLE
fn copy_buffer(src: &[u8], dst: &mut [u8]) {
    for i in 0..src.len() {
        dst[i] = src[i]; // Panic if dst is smaller!
    }
}

// SAFE
fn copy_buffer_safe(src: &[u8], dst: &mut [u8]) -> usize {
    let len = src.len().min(dst.len());
    dst[..len].copy_from_slice(&src[..len]);
    len
}
```

### CWE-190: Integer Overflow

```rust
// VULNERABLE (in release mode)
fn vulnerable_add(a: u32, b: u32) -> u32 {
    a + b // Wraps silently in release!
}

// SAFE: Use checked arithmetic
fn safe_add(a: u32, b: u32) -> Option<u32> {
    a.checked_add(b)
}

// SAFE: Use saturating arithmetic
fn saturating_add(a: u32, b: u32) -> u32 {
    a.saturating_add(b)
}
```

### CWE-416: Use After Free

Rust prevents this at compile time, but watch for:
- Unsafe code with raw pointers
- FFI boundaries
- Self-referential structs

