## Compliance Checklist

### Pre-Release Security Checklist

- [ ] Run `cargo audit` - no known vulnerabilities
- [ ] Run `cargo deny check` - licenses and bans pass
- [ ] Run `cargo clippy -- -D warnings` - no warnings
- [ ] All unsafe blocks have `// SAFETY:` comments
- [ ] Cryptographic code reviewed with `/crypto-review`
- [ ] Input validation on all external boundaries
- [ ] Error messages don't leak sensitive information
- [ ] Dependencies pinned for security-critical crates
- [ ] Fuzzing targets set up for parsers and decoders
- [ ] CHANGELOG updated with security fixes noted

### OWASP Top 10 for Rust

| OWASP Category | Rust Mitigation |
|----------------|-----------------|
| A01 Broken Access Control | Type-safe authorization, newtype patterns |
| A02 Cryptographic Failures | Use `ring`/RustCrypto, never roll your own |
| A03 Injection | Type-safe query builders, validate inputs |
| A04 Insecure Design | Threat modeling, security reviews |
| A05 Security Misconfiguration | Secure defaults, configuration validation |
| A06 Vulnerable Components | `cargo audit`, `cargo deny` |
| A07 Auth Failures | Argon2id for passwords, secure session handling |
| A08 Data Integrity Failures | Signed updates, integrity checks |
| A09 Logging Failures | Structured logging, no sensitive data |
| A10 SSRF | URL validation, allowlists |

